<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 4:34AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Narrow band of heavier snowfall from Cascade to Hobson this
morning...
At 430 AM, a narrow band of heavier snowfall was occurring along
a line from the city of Cascade to Hobson, Visibility is below a
quarter mile at times in open areas because of combination of
falling and blowing snow.
Snowfall rates could approach 1 inch per hour in this band, along
with wind gusts around 30 mph. This band of heavier snowfall
should begin to diminish after 630 AM.
This band of heavier snowfall will affect areas along the Highway
200 corridor from Belt to Eddies Corner.</description>
